The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Extra DA

 The government today announced another instalment of dearness allowance for its employees and teachers with effect from July 1.

 The 3 per cent increase in dearness allowance, which will also benefit pensioners, would cost the exchequer Rs 190 crore. 

 The finance minister said: We will have to restrict the rate of growth of salary and pension.




